1
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:13,430
[school bells ring]

2
00:00:18,852 --> 00:00:22,272
Ren! You and I need to have
a little chat, mister!

3
00:00:26,318 --> 00:00:28,278
[REA]
What's the matter, Ayase?

4
00:00:28,362 --> 00:00:32,199
[KASUMI] Ah... Hi, Rea.
I was just looking for Ren.

5
00:00:32,282 --> 00:00:35,369
I haven't seen him.
Is there a problem?

6
00:00:35,452 --> 00:00:38,247
Kinda. I'm startin to wonder
if he's trying to avoid me

7
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:42,543
or something. He left without
saying anything this morning.

8
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:45,754
[REA] Did you get into
a fight? Anything like that?

9
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:47,422
I've been thinking about it,

10
00:00:47,506 --> 00:00:49,299
and I can't come up
with a single reason.

11
00:00:49,383 --> 00:00:52,302
It's weird. My memories
have been all fuzzy lately.

12
00:00:52,386 --> 00:00:55,430
That must suck.
It sounds confusing.

13
00:00:55,514 --> 00:00:58,058
It totally is, that's why
I wanted to talk to him,

14
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:00,561
but I haven't been able
to find him anywhere.

15
00:01:00,644 --> 00:01:05,399
[shouts] Where'd you
run off to? Ren?!

16
00:01:10,529 --> 00:01:15,492
[REN grunts]

17
00:01:17,619 --> 00:01:18,704
[KEI]
You look like you're in pain.

18
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:20,872
[REN gasps]

19
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:23,083
[KEI] Are you trying to
avoid that friend of yours?

20
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:26,795
That's definitely a good idea.
Right now, you're too dangerous.

21
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:29,715
Shut up. If you don't
need anything from me,

22
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:32,968
why don't you leave? Or else.

23
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:35,804
[KEI] Or else what?
What're you going to do?

24
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:41,226
Kill me? You're too weak.

25
00:01:41,310 --> 00:01:44,396
I'm barely trying,
and you can't break free.

26
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:49,735
If you wanna get stronger,
come here later tonight.

27
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:52,738
I can tutor you in
a number of skills.

28
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:54,156
Like how to use this.

29
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,449
[REN gasps]

30
00:01:55,532 --> 00:02:00,495
♪

31
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:30,043
[VALERIA] And thus,
certain factors of interests

32
00:03:30,127 --> 00:03:33,171
have developed, und the
stage has finally been set.

33
00:03:33,255 --> 00:03:35,882
But of course, nothing in
this world is certain.

34
00:03:35,966 --> 00:03:37,342
I believe there
are still matters

35
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:39,386
that require our
undivided attention.

36
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:41,054
Specifically‐‐

37
00:03:41,138 --> 00:03:42,514
[SPINNE] The war that
Lord Heydrich seeks

38
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:44,474
mustn't be a
half‐hearted engagement.

39
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:46,560
That's what you ought
to say, isn't it?

40
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:49,896
The death of lesser beings will
not grant entry to Valhalla.

41
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:51,523
An enemy must be powerful,

42
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:54,609
und our victory a symbol
of our unrivalled glory.

43
00:03:54,693 --> 00:03:57,696
Ja. Therefore, let us
take another step.

44
00:03:57,779 --> 00:04:00,615
For the benefit of our
Lord Heydrich's return.

45
00:04:00,699 --> 00:04:03,785
As our master's stand‐in
for the present moment,

46
00:04:03,869 --> 00:04:06,705
I issue the following order.

47
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:08,623
For the purpose of
achieving our goal,

48
00:04:08,707 --> 00:04:10,792
we'll assist the enemy.

49
00:04:12,294 --> 00:04:14,588
[KEI]
And that is the situation.

50
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,465
I've been ordered to
make you more competent

51
00:04:16,548 --> 00:04:18,258
and capable in your abilities.

52
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:20,469
Some of my colleagues
opposed the idea.

53
00:04:20,552 --> 00:04:24,598
However, I did not. Which is
why I was assigned to train you.

54
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:27,100
That, as well as the
fact we're the same age.

55
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:29,102
I'd be more empathetic,
in theory,

56
00:04:29,186 --> 00:04:31,354
which would make
it easier to train you.

57
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:33,648
[REN]
What do you mean?

58
00:04:33,732 --> 00:04:35,609
What I mean,

59
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:37,819
Is I'm not nearly as old as
the others in our organization.

60
00:04:37,903 --> 00:04:40,655
I think you'll find that you and
I have a great deal in common.

61
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:42,616
I sincerely doubt that.

62
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,785
Didn't you say your friends
were trying to start a war?

63
00:04:44,868 --> 00:04:48,121
We are, indeed, but this is our
situation, for the time being.

64
00:04:48,205 --> 00:04:50,123
So there's no need to be rash.

65
00:04:50,207 --> 00:04:53,126
And if you want to fight back,
you'll have to get stronger.

66
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:54,085
Got it?

67
00:04:54,169 --> 00:04:55,879
[REN grunts]

68
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,589
[KEI]
To better understand,

69
00:04:57,672 --> 00:04:59,674
I'll start things off
with a basic rundown.

70
00:04:59,758 --> 00:05:01,635
First let me tell
you who we are.

71
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:04,554
As I've mentioned before,
it began generations ago

72
00:05:04,638 --> 00:05:06,723
with a single mage.

73
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:10,685
Mercurius. Karl Krafft.

74
00:05:10,769 --> 00:05:12,312
During World War Two,

75
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:14,689
soldiers and criminals
alike gained power

76
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:16,942
with Mercurius's assistance.

77
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:19,945
Including him,
there were 13 in all.

78
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:23,824
[KEI] They became the
Longinus Dreiztehn Orden

79
00:05:23,907 --> 00:05:27,410
black round table.
That is who we are.

80
00:05:28,829 --> 00:05:31,581
[KEI] But several of our
number are now dead or gone.

81
00:05:31,665 --> 00:05:35,293
Some have been replaced, while
some seats remain unfilled.

82
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:40,882
[KEI] Roughly a decade ago, the
fifth seat became available,

83
00:05:40,966 --> 00:05:44,261
and I've been a sitting
member ever since.

84
00:05:44,344 --> 00:05:46,096
And just like the
rest of the group,

85
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:48,431
I have a wish that
I want to come true.

86
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:50,183
Has anyone told
you about that, yet?

87
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:51,977
[REN] Your friend mentioned
wanting something,

88
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,562
but she didn't say what.

89
00:05:53,645 --> 00:05:55,605
[KEI] Then I won't
reveal it to you either.

90
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:57,732
One's wishes should be private.

91
00:05:57,816 --> 00:05:59,693
[REN exhales]

92
00:05:59,776 --> 00:06:01,444
[KEI] I can tell you that after
everything's been said and done,

93
00:06:01,528 --> 00:06:03,697
we're basically just
a bunch of losers.

94
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,782
We've been a bizarre
group from the beginning.

95
00:06:05,866 --> 00:06:07,742
If we wanted our
dreams to come true,

96
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:10,328
we'd have to make it
happen unconventionally.

97
00:06:10,412 --> 00:06:12,289
[REN]
And so you'll start a war?

98
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:15,667
[KEI] Yes, but to wage a war,
one must have an opponent.

99
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,128
Although he's the second
most important member,

100
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:20,130
we have to rely on Krafft.

101
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:23,758
He promised that at the
right place, and the right time,

102
00:06:23,842 --> 00:06:26,303
the right opponent
will be prepared for us.

103
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:29,931
We shall conquer them,
and make our dreams come true.

104
00:06:30,015 --> 00:06:32,934
Which means, we are
destined to defeat you!

105
00:06:33,018 --> 00:06:35,854
[gasps]
That doesn't make any sense.

106
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:37,480
The hell are you saying?

107
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,774
I haven't got a clue
who you people are,

108
00:06:39,858 --> 00:06:42,110
or who this Mercurius guy is.

109
00:06:42,193 --> 00:06:43,612
That makes no difference.

110
00:06:43,695 --> 00:06:45,906
Clueless or not,
you're the target.

111
00:06:45,989 --> 00:06:48,617
If you don't think it's fair,
complain to Krafft.

112
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,744
All of the veterans
dislike the man.

113
00:06:50,827 --> 00:06:52,787
I've heard that he
can be pretty nasty.

114
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:55,832
As are most of the higher ups.

115
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:57,959
Ever since the last great
war came to an end,

116
00:06:58,043 --> 00:07:00,545
several of them
have disappeared.

117
00:07:00,629 --> 00:07:03,548
Krafft is one of the missing.

118
00:07:03,632 --> 00:07:06,760
I don't know them, but the
word is they're all monsters.

119
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:09,429
Which may be the reason
they were selected.

120
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:12,599
And I've heard if the
war proceeds, they will return.

121
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:14,476
[REN]
So what you're saying is,

122
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:16,227
the guys at the bottom of
the totem pole, like yourself,

123
00:07:16,311 --> 00:07:18,480
have to satisfy the
important ones at the top?

124
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:21,942
That's right. Otherwise my
wish would never come true.

125
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:29,574
Krafft bestowed us with some
incredible magical abilities,

126
00:07:29,658 --> 00:07:31,868
the most important of
which ties us to a weapon,

127
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:34,579
thus imbuing our
bodies with power.

128
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:36,623
These weapons are
known as relics.

129
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:39,084
Most are bound by a curse.

130
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:41,670
They eat the souls of
humans who fall to them.

131
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:45,632
Making us stronger,
and therefore tougher to kill.

132
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:49,052
If we slay a hundred, we gain
the energy of a hundred,

133
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:52,681
which makes us far more powerful
than the average human.

134
00:07:52,764 --> 00:07:55,183
That's why you couldn't
lay a finger on Bey

135
00:07:55,266 --> 00:07:57,227
when he confronted
you in the park.

136
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,688
[KEI] Obviously, kicking and
punching have no effect,

137
00:07:59,771 --> 00:08:02,232
but neither do
firearms or explosives.

138
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:05,026
He has killed countless people
to become that strong.

139
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:07,278
Now, you have the same
potential he did.

140
00:08:07,362 --> 00:08:10,073
You have a weapon that
turns souls into power.

141
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:12,701
Since it's a spell, the more
experienced you are with it,

142
00:08:12,784 --> 00:08:17,080
the more you can do.
But you're still a rank amateur.

143
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:18,957
The lowest level is activity,

144
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,960
next is formation,
then creation.

145
00:08:22,043 --> 00:08:24,004
No one has reached
the highest level,

146
00:08:24,087 --> 00:08:26,381
so what it is exactly,
remains unknown.

147
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:31,594
But as far as you're concerned,
this is where you are. Activity.

148
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:36,182
At this stage, you can activate
your relic with just a thought.

149
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:39,686
For example, blades fire
invisible slashes.

150
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:41,980
That may all seem quite
impressive to you,

151
00:08:42,063 --> 00:08:44,357
but this stage is
highly unstable.

152
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:46,276
Since you haven't
mastered your relic,

153
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:50,030
the power is low, and it's
easy to lose control.

154
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:53,366
At the very least, you need
to reach the formation level.

155
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:55,660
There, your relic can
take on physical form,

156
00:08:55,744 --> 00:08:57,495
and turn into a weapon.

157
00:08:57,579 --> 00:09:00,623
If you can't do that, Fujii,
you won't stand a chance.

158
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:03,835
Which is why, that's what
we'll work on first.

159
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:06,046
We'll start off with the basics.

160
00:09:11,843 --> 00:09:13,053
[REN grunts]

161
00:09:20,769 --> 00:09:21,728
[gasps]

162
00:09:28,485 --> 00:09:29,861
[REN grunts]

163
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:34,115
[gasps] Well look who
came outta hiding!

164
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:37,118
That was totally inconsiderate!
Where the hell have you been?

165
00:09:37,202 --> 00:09:38,995
[REN grunts]

166
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:42,791
Listen. I'm not sure
what happened,

167
00:09:42,874 --> 00:09:45,126
but lately, you've been
acting kinda weird.

168
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:47,170
You even sealed up the
hole in the wall.

169
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:49,506
I guess I might have done some
things that I shouldn't have,

170
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:51,841
but I can't remember.

171
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:54,427
I wanna know if something's
going on with you. Tell me,

172
00:09:54,511 --> 00:09:57,680
did I do something to make you
want to start avoiding me?

173
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:02,227
[REN exhales]

174
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:04,104
[RUSALKA]
What do we have here?

175
00:10:04,187 --> 00:10:06,815
I hope we're not
interrupting anything.

176
00:10:06,898 --> 00:10:09,317
Don't tell me, it's a
little lover's quarrel?

177
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,402
Oh, no. That isn't it.

178
00:10:11,486 --> 00:10:13,947
He started being all weird
and aloof outta nowhere.

179
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:17,200
Did he? You don't say.
Bet I know why.

180
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:19,828
[REN coughs]
I'm sorry, Kasumi.

181
00:10:19,911 --> 00:10:21,746
This isn't how I wanted
you to find out,

182
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:24,666
but I actually started dating
Sakurai just recently.

183
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:26,918
[RUSALKA, KEI, KASUMI gasp]

184
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:29,212
[RUSALKA gasps]
Oh wow! That's great!

185
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:32,632
Wait! Uh... So you
guys are, like, an item?

186
00:10:32,715 --> 00:10:35,677
[REN]
Totally together. Yeah?

187
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:39,722
[KEI grunts] Yes, it's been
a whirlwind romance.

188
00:10:39,806 --> 00:10:42,475
She gets super territorial
about our relationship.

189
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:44,102
I'm trying to be mindful
of her feelings.

190
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:46,104
I hope you understand.

191
00:10:46,187 --> 00:10:50,525
I'm sorry. But from now on,
it's my job to look after Fujii.

192
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:53,611
I do appreciate you taking
care of him for this long.

193
00:10:53,695 --> 00:10:56,614
[KASUMI]
Oh! Sure. I understand.

194
00:10:56,698 --> 00:10:58,950
I apologize for
being so oblivious.

195
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:02,203
[chuckles nervously]

196
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:08,209
[KEI, REN grunt]

197
00:11:12,547 --> 00:11:16,801
It's not fair. I thought we...

198
00:11:16,885 --> 00:11:18,386
[KASUMI grunts]

199
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:21,306
I'm so sorry about that!
I wasn't watching.

200
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,609
[SPINNE chuckles]

201
00:11:36,196 --> 00:11:38,781
[REN] Of course.
Finally, I understand.

202
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:40,783
You're the soul that resides
within the guillotine,

203
00:11:40,867 --> 00:11:42,285
isn't that right?

204
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:47,999
When did that happen?
And how is that even possible?

205
00:11:49,334 --> 00:11:53,713
I can touch you, just like
Cagliostro said I could.

206
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:58,927
You're still fine, even though
I'm touching you. I'm happy.

207
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:01,179
Your face is so warm.

208
00:12:01,262 --> 00:12:02,764
[REN gasps]

209
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:07,435
[MARIE] Ren. I know it.
I'm sure you can.

210
00:12:10,021 --> 00:12:12,899
I'm not entirely
comfortable around blades.

211
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:16,152
Whenever I see them, bad
memories come flooding back.

212
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:21,366
But you. You're a good person,
aren't you? I can sense that.

213
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:25,411
And I want to help, because
you deserve to be happy too.

214
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:35,964
[REA] Hey sleepy‐head.
What are you doing?

215
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:39,092
[RIZA]
Good evening.

216
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:41,844
We're out looking for Padre
Goldilocks. Have you seen him?

217
00:12:41,928 --> 00:12:45,807
Ya mean Father Trifa?
No, I'm afraid I haven't.

218
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,809
Why do you ask?

219
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:49,852
Because Rea here is perpetually
saying scathing things to him.

220
00:12:49,936 --> 00:12:51,646
So this is my fault now?

221
00:12:51,729 --> 00:12:53,731
Well, it certainly wasn't
because of what I said!

222
00:12:53,815 --> 00:12:56,734
So, he ran away from home
because you were mean to him?

223
00:12:56,818 --> 00:12:59,195
You know what? You're a
rotten judge of people.

224
00:12:59,279 --> 00:13:00,905
He's actually nothing
like he seems.

225
00:13:00,989 --> 00:13:03,866
[RIZA chuckles]
Well, that's the situation.

226
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:06,703
You be careful out
there too, okay? Chuse!

227
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:10,999
[REA] Wait, Riza. I wasn't
done talking. So rude!

228
00:13:11,082 --> 00:13:12,208
[REN gasps]

229
00:13:16,379 --> 00:13:17,714
[REN grunts]

230
00:13:25,847 --> 00:13:27,765
Well, that's bizarre.

231
00:13:27,849 --> 00:13:30,476
I'm positive he came this way
before I lost sight of him.

232
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:37,900
[VALERIA]
Hello.

233
00:13:37,984 --> 00:13:39,485
[REN gasps]

234
00:13:39,569 --> 00:13:42,488
[VALERIA]
Is something the matter, Fujii?

235
00:13:42,572 --> 00:13:45,491
Fancy running into you
in a place like this.

236
00:13:45,575 --> 00:13:47,076
Did you need something?

237
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,454
No sir. I, uh...

238
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:52,165
[VALERIA chuckles] I can
assume those two asked you

239
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:54,125
to look for me, didn't they?

240
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:56,419
It's all quite embarrassing when
you stop to think about it.

241
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:58,755
It's patently obvious those
ladies don't hold me

242
00:13:58,838 --> 00:13:59,964
in the highest of regards.

243
00:14:00,048 --> 00:14:01,841
I'm sure that isn't true.

244
00:14:01,924 --> 00:14:04,677
If you ask me, I think they
were worried about you.

245
00:14:04,761 --> 00:14:06,888
Maybe it's time for you
to head back to the church.

246
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:10,683
Yes, perhaps. But then,
in my own way,

247
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:13,353
I'm concerned for
Theresia as well.

248
00:14:13,436 --> 00:14:17,565
It's truly depressing that
she fails to understand that.

249
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:21,903
By the way, I was wondering if
you were in love with Theresia.

250
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:23,112
[REN]
Uh...

251
00:14:25,156 --> 00:14:28,743
Sorry. I suppose that was
a bit of an odd question.

252
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:29,786
Farewell, then.

253
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:31,371
[REN]
Uh, wait!

254
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,251
[REN gasps]

255
00:14:38,669 --> 00:14:39,879
[gasps]

256
00:14:42,632 --> 00:14:47,762
[REN] Impossible.
I imagined it. I must have.

257
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:52,809
[phone ringing]

258
00:14:54,519 --> 00:14:57,814
What's up? Is everything okay?

259
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:59,524
Yo, Kasumi, hey!

260
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:04,112
[KASUMI gasps]
Ren... Please... Help me.

261
00:15:04,195 --> 00:15:08,324
[SPINNE laughs] Your girlfriend
is a real cutie‐pie.

262
00:15:08,408 --> 00:15:11,244
Makes me want to
gobble her right up!

263
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:14,372
My name's Rotte Spinne,
und I love your work.

264
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:18,668
[REN grunts] Listen. You messed
with the wrong person.

265
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:20,837
That's your last mistake.

266
00:15:35,017 --> 00:15:36,185
[REN gasps]

267
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:42,984
[REN grunts]

268
00:15:53,578 --> 00:15:54,745
[gasps]

269
00:15:54,829 --> 00:15:57,248
[SPINNE chuckles]

270
00:15:57,331 --> 00:15:59,292
[REN]
You bastard!

271
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:03,254
Welcome, dear boy! You're just
in time for tonight's feast!

272
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:06,090
Allow me to introduce
myself more formally.

273
00:16:06,174 --> 00:16:08,676
The Tenth seat of the
Longinus Dreizehn Orden

274
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:13,973
black round table, Rotte Spinne.
Und it's a pleasure to meet you.

275
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:16,309
[REN grunts]

276
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:17,894
[SPINNE]
It's useless, boy.

277
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:20,605
Right now, you can't
cut through them.

278
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:22,982
Leonhart was supposed to
have explained it to you.

279
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:26,319
I'm using the formation level.
Here, the relic can be given

280
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:28,529
tangible form to
create a weapon.

281
00:16:28,613 --> 00:16:30,114
[REN gasps]

282
00:16:30,198 --> 00:16:31,365
If you can't compete
on the same level,

283
00:16:31,449 --> 00:16:32,950
then you haven't got a chance.

284
00:16:33,034 --> 00:16:35,578
Just like everything
else in this life.

285
00:16:41,501 --> 00:16:44,629
[SPINNE shouts]

286
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:46,422
[REN grunts]

287
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:48,466
Your eyes show the fire
that is in your spirit.

288
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:51,219
I must say, it's quite
inspiring to behold.

289
00:16:51,302 --> 00:16:53,054
I'm sure you've been told this.

290
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:56,140
But we all truly wish for
you to become stronger.

291
00:16:56,224 --> 00:16:58,851
And so, Leonhart will
provide the lectures,

292
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:01,521
and I will administer the
practical examination

293
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:03,439
to see what you've learned.

294
00:17:03,523 --> 00:17:05,107
But just between the two of us,

295
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:07,109
I have no intention of
becoming your enemy,

296
00:17:07,193 --> 00:17:09,195
despite what the
others may desire.

297
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:11,405
[gasps]
The hell do you mean?

298
00:17:11,489 --> 00:17:13,866
There were no hidden
meanings in what I said.

299
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:16,244
Honestly, I'm not like
the rest of my order.

300
00:17:16,327 --> 00:17:19,205
Und although I believe you
will help us reach our goal,

301
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:22,458
you must prove that you
can do the work required.

302
00:17:24,627 --> 00:17:27,296
[REN gasps]

303
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:29,715
[shouts]

304
00:17:29,799 --> 00:17:31,342
Don't be afraid to cut loose.

305
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:33,886
I want you to show
me vhat you've got!

306
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:37,265
[gasps]

307
00:17:37,974 --> 00:17:40,351
[shouts]

308
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:44,689
[laughs]

309
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:48,526
Wow, she fell to pieces!
Now you will show me!

310
00:17:49,777 --> 00:17:52,613
[REN grunts]

311
00:17:52,697 --> 00:17:53,489
[gasps]

312
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:58,494
[REN shouts]

313
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:07,878
[REN grunts]

314
00:18:07,962 --> 00:18:09,672
Are you serious?

315
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:12,466
I want only to see your power,
not your insanity!

316
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:14,010
[SPINNE gasps]

317
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:18,639
[REN grunts]
I'll kill you. I swear.

318
00:18:18,723 --> 00:18:21,225
I'll kill you, bastard!

319
00:18:22,351 --> 00:18:24,312
Formation!

320
00:18:42,204 --> 00:18:43,831
That's something!

321
00:18:43,914 --> 00:18:46,792
So the child of a monster
is himself a monster!

322
00:18:46,876 --> 00:18:48,502
[shouts]

323
00:18:58,512 --> 00:19:00,181
Well then, so be it!

324
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:02,892
If that's the case,
it's time for a real show!

325
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:07,980
[SPINNE, REN shout, grunt]

326
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:14,945
What?

327
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:25,247
[gasps]

328
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,252
[REN growls]

329
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:32,213
Wait, no! You're taking
this too far.

330
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:34,715
Priest of the Grail!
Come save me!

331
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:36,175
[SPINNE gasps]

332
00:19:39,136 --> 00:19:40,888
[VALERIA]
Hm...

333
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:43,641
Don't underestimate me!
Did you think that was it?

334
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:46,602
That I'd make a move
without any insurance?

335
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:51,857
[gasps]

336
00:19:51,941 --> 00:19:53,859
No, of course not.

337
00:19:53,943 --> 00:19:56,112
But did you honestly think I
couldn't guess what you'd do?

338
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:59,699
Farewell, Spinne.
Die within the swastika.

339
00:19:59,782 --> 00:20:00,783
[gasps]

340
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:02,410
[REN shouts]

341
00:20:02,493 --> 00:20:07,915
[SPINNE groans]

342
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:16,757
[SPINNE]
Mein Gott! Not yet... No!

343
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:31,897
[REA grunts]

344
00:20:32,857 --> 00:20:34,150
[gasps]

345
00:21:03,179 --> 00:21:05,931
[KASUMI grunts]
It isn't in here, either?

346
00:21:06,015 --> 00:21:07,224
Where could it have gone?

347
00:21:07,308 --> 00:21:09,393
‐‐[door rattles]
‐‐[KASUMI gasps]

348
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:14,732
[KASUMI gasps]
Oh! Sorry, I barged in.

349
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:16,776
I seem to have
misplaced my phone,

350
00:21:16,859 --> 00:21:19,487
and thought that it might have
somehow ended up in your room.

351
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:21,489
And there's also a
bunch of random things

352
00:21:21,572 --> 00:21:23,240
I left here scattered around,
and I thought Sakurai might

353
00:21:23,324 --> 00:21:26,327
get mad if she came by
and found all my stuff.

354
00:21:27,912 --> 00:21:33,459
Kasumi... I'm so glad
you're here. I mean it.

355
00:21:44,762 --> 00:21:49,725
♪

